choices.text:
sleeping.

As a teenager in Istanbul, my biggest problem is….. Well, I really have nothing to complain about at all.

As a teenager in Malaysia my biggest problem is….. on reflection , its actually quite difficult to figure any out.

I scare myself a bit here. What can I say I remember working on it as a teenager and having great scholastic success so what happens now I compare with last time rather than what I know now which can’t be good for my ego. As a more mature I thought, with reflection, one good thing was the regular reminders to check my vision and ears back in my late teens. My vision is still my friends but the deafness has really taken a grip now and I suppose my vision could be a little better even dialating my pupils before I leave the house on occasions to avoid bushes. Otherwise at 60 my biggest problems are physical but not sure that is what you were looking for. So beggers can’t be choosers much as I appreciate the idea of a challenge you get what you’re given. So another joyous day in lockdown 2020 but tomorrow things are due to change. Out of curiosity what’s the greatest courage you have shown in the past year?

So the 2021 version of myself half way down the blog will be able to make a more meaningful comment here. I have knee problems, Thank you AS, and had a knee replacement at the start of November, but there are others on here who have much
